parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause a loss of visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions. This can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Headlights turn off randomly
flicker
or go out without warning
often requiring the driver to turn the lights off and on again to restore function. This issue can occur while driving
stationary
or on different road types.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive glare from LED headlights can cause temporary blindness, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: LED headlights are too bright
causing glare that makes it difficult to see the road
especially when driving in the opposite direction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to unpredictable and dangerous braking, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
warning lights on the dashboard
and unusual noises when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Infiltration into the Brake Control Power Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water infiltration into the brake control power module can cause the module to short out and fail, leading to a loss of regenerative braking and a brake warning light.
symptoms: Water damage to the brake control power module
loss of regenerative braking
and brake warning light on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the combination meter can cause the instrument panel to go dark, making it impossible to see the speedometer, fuel gauge, and warning lights, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The instrument panel goes dark
the speedometer and fuel gauge do not display
the warning lights do not illuminate
the backup camera does not function
and the vehicle may not shut off properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the dashboard lights and warning lights do not function
the backup camera does not display
and the vehicle may not shut off properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: One or both headlights do not function
the headlights shut off intermittently
or the bulb burns out frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brakes do not function properly
the brake lights do not illuminate
or the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil level indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of low oil levels, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The oil level indicator does not function
the oil warning light does not illuminate
or the oil level drops rapidly.
